      <div1 id="BQ-39-4-0007">
        <head>
          <title type="section">CORRIGENDUM</title>
        </head>
        <byline>By <docAuthor>Robert N. <name>Essick</name></docAuthor></byline>
        <p>In “A (Self?) Portrait of William Blake,” <hi rend="i">Blake</hi> 39.3 (winter 2005-06): 137, I
claimed that the “Meyer” to whom Hayley refers as having helped Blake learn miniature portraiture in 1801
was “probably . . . Jeremiah Meyer.” He died in 1789, and thus Blake’s instructor must have been
Jeremiah’s son, William, also a miniaturist.</p>
      </div1>
